period of thought. I thought that White should prepare a plan based on c2-c3,
Nd2-b3c5, dxc5 and Nd4, but this seems not so easy to implement.} (12. Nb3 c5
$1) (12. Qf2 Qe7 13. O-O O-O-O 14. Nb3 Kb8 15. c3 Qd6 16. Nc5 Nxc5 17. dxc5 Qc6
18. Rac1 g4 $1 19. Nh4 h5 20. Nf5 Bxf5 21. Bxf5 d4 $17) ({It is probably best
to prepare a slower attack with} 12. c3 Qe7 13. O-O O-O-O 14. b4 Kb8 15. Nb3
Rde8 16. Nc5 Nxc5 17. bxc5 Bc8 18. Qc2 c6 $13 {Strategically, Black is doing
great, but due to the castling on opposite sides the position remains sharp.})
12... g4 13. Nh4 {The most principled continuation. White sacrifices a pawn
for the initiative. It will turn out that Black is in time to complete his
development with at least some advantage.} (13. Ne5 Nxe5 14. dxe5 Qg5 15. Rae1
O-O 16. c3 c5 $15) 13... Bxd4+ 14. Kh1 Qg5 15. Ng6 (15. Bf5 O-O-O 16. Bxe6 fxe6
{[%csl Rd2] XNd2}) (15. Nf5 Bxb2 16. Rab1 Bc3 {[%csl Rd2]}) 15... Rg8 16. Nb3 (
16. Nf4 Qe5 17. Rae1 O-O-O 18. c3 Qxe2 19. Rxe2 Be5 $15) 16... Bb6 ({I thought
that there was no need for radical measures such as} 16... Bxb2 $5 17. Rab1 Bc3
