O-O N7g6 $17 {Boehsmueller,R (2175)-Poeltl,T (2210) Austria 1998 (0-1, 20)})
4... exd5 5. Nf3 Nc6 6. Bb5 (6. d4 Nf6 {leads to a very pleasant isolani
position, as the c3-square is weak.}) 6... Qe7+ $1 (6... Nf6 $6 7. Qe2+ {
would result in doubled pawns on the f-file after Bxf6.}) 7. Be2 (7. Qe2 Qxe2+
