Nxd4 Nxd4 13. Bxd4 {Minasian,A (2570)-Nedobora,M (2435) Oviedo 1993 (0-1, 65)}
Qc7 14. Nf1 Rac8 15. c4 Bf6 16. Ne3 a6 $11 {, with a comfortable Hedgehog.})
11... b5 12. Ne3 Bf6 13. c3 (13. Qc1 Bxb2 14. Qxb2 Qf6 15. Qc1 a6 16. Qd2 Nde5
17. Nxe5 dxe5 $11 {Tsydypov,Z (2523)-Lysyj,I (2618) Khanty-Mansiysk 2017 (0-1,
44)}) 13... Nde5 14. Qd2 a5 15. d4 Nxf3+ 16. Bxf3 a4 {, with good counterplay
in a complex position, Florean,A (2441)-Simantsev,M (2403) Bucharest 2000 (1/
2-1/2 64)}) (7. Nbd2 {[%emt 0:00:17] is examined in Line}) (7. Nh4 {does not
have much independent value either, as White will have to develop his queen's
knight soon, while his kingside attack is not too dangerous before Black has
castled.} Nc6 8. f4 Be7 {. The same goes for moves like 7.Re1 or 7.Qe2. Black
can continue in the spirit of the main lines examined below.}) 7... Be7 8. Ne1
{The start of a slow but consistent kingside attack.} (8. Re1 a6 9. d4 cxd4 10.
Nxd4 {reaches an inoffensive Scheveningen setup with a tempo less for White.}
Qc7 11. g4 (11. a4 Nc6 12. Nde2 O-O 13. h3 Rfd8 14. Nf4 Rac8 15. Nd3 Nd7 16.
Ne2 Nce5 17. Nd4 Nc5 $11 {Damljanovic,B (2596)-Sedlak,N (2553) Vrsac 2008 (0-1,
69)}) 11... O-O ({Caution is required:} 11... Nc6 $2 12. g5 Nd7 13. Nf5 exf5 $2
14. Nd5 Qd8 15. exf5 $16) 12. g5 Nfd7 13. a4 Re8 ({The careless} 13... Nc6 {
allowed} 14. Nd5 $1 $14 {in Tosic,M (2416)-Zivkovic,N (2198) Nis 2012 (0-1, 33)
, as the bishop is hanging after the opening of the e-file.}) 14. f4 Nc6 $11) (
8. Nh4 {can be met in similar way as the main plan:} Nc6 (8... Nfd7 9. f4 Bxh4
10. gxh4 Qxh4 {allows} 11. Nb5 $1) 9. f4 Qd7) 8... Nc6 9. f4 Qd7 $5 $146 {
In most games Black castles short early. I believe this untested move is
better, as it keeps the possibility of castling long open, if White commits
himself too much on the kingside.} 10. Bd2 (10. g4 O-O-O 11. g5 Ne8 {allows
Black to open the kingside with dangerous counterplay.}) (10. Be3 {exposes the
bishop to} d5 11. e5 d4 $1) ({The flexible} 10. Nf3 {delays g3-g4, so Black
can already play} O-O ({Instead,} 10... O-O-O 11. a3 {looks dangerous, as
Black's kingside play is not that obvious.}) 11. h3 Rad8 12. g4 Ne8 13. g5 Nc7
14. h4 f5 $11) 10... O-O-O 11. a3 h5 {Play is likely to become sharp. Here is
